heap-buddy
------------------------------------------
Heap-Buddy is a summarizing memory profiling tool for Mono.  It attaches 
to special hooks in the Mono runtime and tracks all of the managed 
memory allocations, every garbage collection, and every heap resize.  
The statistics are written out into a data file that can then be 
analyzed by the heap-buddy tool.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  mono-1.2.2.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.2.9-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  libtool1.5-1.5.23a-2
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.21-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.mono-project.com/

Canonical download:
  http://go-mono.com/sources-stable/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack heap-buddy-0.2-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./heap-buddy-0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/heap-buddy-0.2-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/heap-buddy-0.2-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/cygmono-profiler-heap-buddy.dll
  /usr/bin/heap-buddy
  /usr/lib/heap-buddy/HeapBuddy.exe
  /usr/lib/libmono-profiler-heap-buddy.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libmono-profiler-heap-buddy.la
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/heap-buddy-0.2.README
  /usr/share/doc/heap-buddy-0.2/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/heap-buddy-0.2/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/heap-buddy-0.2/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/heap-buddy-0.2/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/heap-buddy-0.2/README

